type="machine">unstable/6126</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-6126.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="The coherent remainder of a section is a proposition › "><fr:link
href="erct-0043.xml"
title="The coherent remainder of a section is a proposition"
addr="erct-0043"
type="local">The <fr:link
href="erct-0041.xml"
title="The coherent remainder of a section"
addr="erct-0041"
type="local">coherent remainder</fr:link> of a <fr:link
href="erct-000Y.xml"
title="Section-retraction pair"
addr="erct-000Y"
type="local">section</fr:link> is a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
title="Proposition"
addr="erct-001I"
type="local">proposition</fr:link></fr:link> › </fr:title><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>By <fr:link
href="erct-0026.xml"
title="Propositions are closed under retracts"
addr="erct-0026"
type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number
addr="erct-0026" /></fr:link>, we may argue that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{f}\sigma ]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
href="erct-0025.xml"
title="Retract"
addr="erct-0025"
type="local">retract</fr:link> of a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
title="Proposition"
addr="erct-001I"
type="local">proposition</fr:link>. We let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> be the following type defined using <fr:link
href="erct-0010.xml"
title="Path object"
addr="erct-0010"
type="local">path object</fr:link> structure of <fr:link
href="erct-001Q.xml"
title="Fiber"
addr="erct-001Q"
type="local">fibers</fr:link> given in <fr:link
href="erct-001R.xml"
title="Path object structure on fibers"
addr="erct-001R"
type="local">Example <fr:contextual-number
addr="erct-001R" /></fr:link>:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {aligned}
   P &:\equiv 
   \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}
   
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen g
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
,\epsilon 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen fx\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}

   \cong _{\mathsf {fiber}\,f\,
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen fx\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}
   
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,\mathsf {refl}\right \rparen \mathclose {}

   \\
   P &\equiv 
   \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}
   \mathchoice {\textstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen p : g
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 = x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen p : g
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 = x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen p : g
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 = x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen p : g
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 = x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}
   \epsilon 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen fx\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 = \mathsf {act}_{f}p\cdot  \mathsf {refl}
  \end {aligned}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>It is not difficult to show using <fr:link
href="erct-0042.xml"
title="Coherent remainder as a path object"
addr="erct-0042"
type="local">Definition <fr:contextual-number
addr="erct-0042" /></fr:link> that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{f}\sigma ]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
href="erct-0025.xml"
title="Retract"
addr="erct-0025"
type="local">retract</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex>; we will not need the further fact that it is <fr:em>equivalent</fr:em> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>Therefore, it remains to show that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
title="Proposition"
addr="erct-001I"
type="local">proposition</fr:link>. Without loss of generality, we may assume that we have some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[h: P]]></fr:tex>. By <fr:link
href="erct-001B.xml"
title="Dependent product of propositions"
addr="erct-001B"
type="local">Corollary <fr:contextual-number
addr="erct-001B" /></fr:link>, we may fix <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x:A]]></fr:tex> and prove that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen g
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
,\epsilon 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen fx\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\cong _{\mathsf {fiber}\,f\,
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen fx\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,\mathsf {refl}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
title="Proposition"
addr="erct-001I"
type="local">proposition</fr:link>. Of course, this is a <fr:link
href="erct-0025.xml"
title="Retract"
addr="erct-0025"
type="local">retract</fr:link> of the identification type <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen g
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
,\epsilon 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen fx\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
=_{\mathsf {fiber}\,f\,
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen fx\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,\mathsf {refl}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex> and so by <fr:link
href="erct-0026.xml"
title="Propositions are closed under retracts"
addr="erct-0026"
type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number
addr="erct-0026" /></fr:link> it is enough to prove that the latter is a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
title="Proposition"
addr="erct-001I"
type="local">proposition</fr:link>. In fact, we will deduce this via <fr:link
href="erct-002T.xml"
title="Truncation is upward closed"
addr="erct-002T"
type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number
addr="erct-002T" /></fr:link> by observing that the <fr:link
href="erct-001Q.xml"
title="Fiber"
addr="erct-001Q"
type="local">fiber</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> at <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[fx]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="erct-001H.xml"
title="Contractible type"
addr="erct-001H"
type="local">contractible</fr:link>: using our assumption <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[h:P]]></fr:tex> and the distributivity of products over sums, we may construct a retraction of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> exhibiting <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> as <fr:link
href="erct-000U.xml"
title="Biinverse"
addr="erct-000U"
type="local">biinvertible</fr:link> and thus by <fr:link
href="erct-002N.xml"
title="Biinvertible maps are contractible"
addr="erct-002N"
type="local">Corollary <fr:contextual-number
addr="erct-002N" /></fr:link> <fr:link
href="erct-001T.xml"
title="n-truncated map"
addr="erct-001T"
type="local">contractible</fr:link>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
